author: @efyoubadly
text: in the end just add 'Score model' and connect 'Trained model o/p data to the left part of 'score model' and right part of the score model to the test data from split data.( which is 0.3 ) . Now in the score model visualize, you will get last two columns.. with the actual test data result and probability obtained from the Trained model. If its value close to the test data model works fine. ( Try to increase depth of the tree to get more accurate result ). for eg. 32 ( Don't make it too large )

text: Thank you for another great lesson. Naturally, my tree and yours were different, this is the reason you need a forest after all. But I have a question.
